 What we want to accomplish and why we need you? 
 
Haptik is one of the world's largest Conversational AI companies, having reached over 100 million devices, and processed over 2 billion conversations till date. Haptik has been at the forefront of the paradigm shift of interaction from clicks to conversations. We have built a robust set of technology and tools that can enable any kind of conversational application. With a 100-member strong team, including some of the finest minds in Artificial Intelligence, Haptik is truly poised to lead the Conversational AI revolution. We are building bots for all sizes, big and small - come and join us! 
 
We are on the lookout for a dynamic individual in the Inside Sales Team who specializes in lead generation and have experience in building a list of fresh, relevant and geo-targeted prospects based on your target market. 
 
What will you do every day? 
 Research & extract relevant details about companies, senior executives by using different research processes on the internet. 
 Generate high quality leads from LinkedIn and websites through various tools and extensions. 
 Manage and extract required data from all incoming data files coming from sources such as exhibitions, events, etc. 
 Manage master data, including creation, updates, and deletion for the inside-sales team to run outbound sales activities. Be hands-on with various tools like LinkedIn, HubSpot, MS Office which the Inside sales team uses 
 Review data for inconsistencies or anomalies. 
 Ok, you're sold, but what are we looking for in the perfect candidate? 
 Excellent communication skills. Remember communication is not what you say but what other people understand. 
 Work with cross-functional teams, internal and external with ease and drive them towards a common goal. 
 Handle large datasets (structured & unstructured) 
 Maintain MIS of Data collation & Compilation 
 Can adapt to change and is open to learning new skills 
 A quick learner with an ability to work as part of a team 
 Requirements* 
 Bachelor's degree in Marketing, Businesses Administration, Business Management, or related field. 
 Experience 0-2 years 
 Strong analytical and problem-solving skills 
 Excellent ability to work with large data sets 
 Good organizational skills 
 Good verbal and written communication skills 
 
